verse:
“See, I will break the bow of Elam, the mainstay of their might. 36 I will bring against Elam the four winds from the four quarters of heaven;
I will scatter them to the four winds, and there will not be a nation where Elam’s exiles do not go. 37 I will shatter Elam before their foes, before those who want to kill them;
I will bring disaster on them, even my fierce anger,”
declares the Lord.
“I will pursue them with the sword until I have made an end of them. 38 I will set my throne in Elam and destroy her king and officials,”
declares the Lord.
